Description: Website
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: DollarOne.com is a website where local businesses sell their products and services for $1.01. Businesses are also offering an extra percentage off if the client decides to buy something else once he/she visits the store. (ex. appetizer for $1.01+30% off the entire food bill). Businesses are self-listing those deals, so they can decide the number of deals, the day/s of the week when they can be redeemed, down to the specific time-frame (ex: 3x manicure services on Sunday and Tuesday between 10am and 8 pm).  http://www.adollarone.com/products/detail/127/classic-spa-manicure/ (link to the actual live deal). Why would businesses want to offer products and services for $1.01 on our website?  Just some of the key reasons: • To offset slow business on specific days and hours • To convert excess/perishable inventory into regular customers • To have an opportunity to up-sell these consumers once in the door • To introduce new products and services  • To provide consumers with a strong incentive to visit their businesses Why would consumers want to use this website? Because of the extraordinary savings • Because of the low cost and low risk commitment • Because they can try/test products/services for just $1.01. • Because we have yet to find someone who wouldn’t! We will be generating revenue from multiple sources, including $5 per month from businesses (they can list an unlimited number of deals), the retention of the $1.01 paid by consumers, the $1.01 one-time business verification fee, and various marketing and promotional programs. Market conditions are favorable and offer a significant opportunity for growth. More than 75 million consumers browse the internet for savings each month, while businesses have increasingly taken advantage of online promotional programs totaling nearly $12 billion. Adolarone.com delivers a unique, innovative web-based service – a fully integrated, all-encompassing web portal that connects businesses with customers offering products and services in a whole new format. Adolarone.com was launched on February 1, 2010 in the greater Los Angeles market. Venturino Piccolo and Nadine Curias own and operate the company.  To achieve the company’s objectives, Golden Piccolo, LLC is seeking $450,000 in total funding through outside investment.   The benefits of this revolutionary sales channel include:  • Great way to introduce new products to the market • Businesses can list offers for certain days or certain hours to offset slow business. Businesses will pay per customer and not per click or per traditional advertising space.  • Consumers are given the chance to try and test new stuff for as little as $1.01. • Members will have to register before they buy, giving the company's demographic information. Businesses will not be charged pay-per-print fees. • Dramatically reduce the waste associated with unused products and services. • Businesses could encourage repeat patronage by offering another coupon once the client has walked through their door. •With the company handling all of the monetary transactions, it can accommodate small businesses that do not have an online payment system of their own. Pay-Per-Click versus Pay-Per-Customer Model AdolLARONE.com enables pay per customer, as opposed to pay per click, marketing. Businesses pay nothing to post coupons on the company’s website and lose only the revenue that would have been gained from selling the product or service at full price. In many situations, this revenue was already lost as the product would have expired or the service slot would not have been filled. Instead of complete waste, the business has gained a customer that will potentially return to the business for future products and services at full price. In the company’s pay-per-customer model, each business only “pays” for the customers that redeem the coupons, as opposed to pay-per-click models where advertisers are charged for every person that clicks an online advertisement, regardless of whether that person then buys anything from the business or becomes a patron. This pay-per-customer model is a huge advance in online advertising and a revolutionary method of combining web models to unite consumers and businesses.
Industry Groups: Advertising, Commerce and Shopping, Sales and Marketing

Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: The Dark Energy Survey (DES) is designed to probe the origin of the accelerating universe and help uncover the nature of dark energy by measuring the 14-billion-year history of cosmic expansion with high precision. More than 120 scientists from 23 institutions in the United States, Spain, the United Kingdom, Brazil, and Germany are working on the project. This collaboration has built and deployed an extremely sensitive 570-Megapixel digital camera, DECam. This new camera has been mounted on the Blanco 4-meter telescope at Cerro Tololo Inter-American Observatory, high in the Chilean Andes. Starting in August of 2013 and continuing for five years, DES has begun to survey a large swath of the southern sky out to vast distances in order to provide new clues to this most fundamental of questions.

Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Myndnet is an information marketplace -- a marketplace that allows anyone with knowledge to share it and get paid for it. Businesses or individuals ask questions and the community responds Palo Alto-based Myndnet believes that the people who answer our questions should get paid for it and has set up their marketplace to accomplish that. The process is quite simple. First, a business client posts a request for candidates and leads on Myndnet using a simple online form. Myndnet's clients are primarily recruiters looking for candidates. The request is posted on the Myndnet website. It is also distributed to a large audience through an RSS feed, and displayed on partner websites, in the form of a "widget". Members can then login to the Myndnet website and submit responses to the requests. The original clients purchase submitted responses and Myndnet pays contributing members for delivering accurate responses. Myndnet users can refer friends to the system and receive additional compensation  The service has a similar model to the now dead Google Answers. Competitors include [LinkedIn Answers](http://www.linkedin.com/answers) as well as [Spoke](http://www.spoke.com/).

Our mission is to provide a network where pregnant women and moms connect with each other to seek and provide advice.  Bloom wants to be the first disruptive force dealing with everyday issues that moms face by creating a P2P network for advice, discussions, connections, sharing and trading. Bloom, originally called Pregnancy Tracker, was created by Manuj Bahl in response to his wife's frustration with the lack of quality pregnancy apps and resources available. When welcoming a new kid to the family we realized there is a real need to pregnant women and new moms to be able to connect and talk with each other. These women would rather talk to strangers who can understand them than friends who have no clue what their needs and concerns are. That is when we decided to build an active community where concerns, solutions, thoughts, ideas & care can easily flow between members. We have a prototype already available & seen enough traction to prove a market.

Full Description: Start-up company, miWi-Fi.net, LLC is a minority, Veteran and Native American owned installation and integration firm focusing on rural wireless broadband services, municipal Wi-Fi and Aruba Networks Bring Your Own Device (BYOB) deployments.  They will operate as a Wireless Internet Service Provider (WISP) building their own network and network back office for routing internet and Voice Over Internet Protocol (VoIP) traffic. Company Background Their service will provide high speed broadband to rural areas that are currently under served by the local incumbent providers. The service will include high speed internet access equivalent to DSL speeds or greater, voice over IP (VoIP) and video services in rural, economically disadvantaged areas. In Madison County Alabama there are areas that do not have the option of high speed internet access due to the population, terrain features and cost of network deployment. It is their goal to use a combination of WiMAX (802.16d/e-2004) and a Wi-Fi delivery solution to provide these services as the cost of network deployment is low and it will cover a large geographic area with the desired broadband coverage. Some residents and businesses are currently using dial up access and are paying a high price for T1 services from Local Exchange Carriers (LEC’s) and Competitive Local Exchange Carriers (CLEC’s). The delivery of their service is what will differentiate us from the competition and gives us a competitive edge. Their rollout costs are lower and provide a quicker ROI to their investors.
